rComments: Having a non-indigenous person teach an indigenous studies class can always be challenging, but she handled it extremely well. Structuring class as more of a discussion provided the opportunity to let others tackle tricky topics and present perspectives she would not be able to alone. This approach created a great amount of respect for her
Bon professeur. Le cours est assez difficile mais il est toujours possible de bien faire avec des efforts. Elle est là pour aider en dehors de la salle de classe.

Really difficult course. The essay was also really hard to write, I spent a week on it and I did in the 70s...  The final exam was also hard, with long answer development questions. It is really hard to do well with her because it is really hard to listen/follow her explanations. She's really nice however I don't recommend

Dr Guimont-Marceau is a really approachable professor, her expectations are not so clear but if you want to do well she's willing to help you. Her course was really interesting although not my favourite GEG class. Efforts are required for this course. Good & caring professor and her exams are open book!

This is the worst geography class I ever took. She is really not a good professor, her explanations are really abstract and impossible to follow. I had no choice to take her, but I dont recommend. Her corrections are really picky and strict. If you want a high mark in this class, I suggest another prof or the English section. Avoid at all costs

Hard course, even the prof doesnt get half the stuff. Powerpoints are horribly organised with quotes instead of clear informations. Lots and lots of stuff to read outside of class. 6 page paper to hand in. Exams are short answers and really hard/specific!
